{"title":"Carriage of dangerous goods authorisation 453","public_updated_at":"2015-09-03T08:30:00Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>This authorisation comes into immediate effect and remains valid until 31 December 2015 unless otherwise revoked.</p>\n\n<p>This authorisation allows deviations from the European requirements for transporting dangerous goods within Great Britain. It permits the continued use of road tank vehicles manufactured by GRW Engineering that are nominally empty.</p>\n\n<p>The table included lists the vehicles that are nominally empty and are being transported for cleaning only and meet conditions set out in the authorisation.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"background-to-carriage-of-dangerous-goods-authorisations\">Background to carriage of dangerous goods authorisations</h2>\n\n<p>The Secretary of State for Transport for transport, can issue <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/transporting-dangerous-goods\">written authorisations</a> that allow for deviations from the requirements of <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.unece.org/trans/danger/publi/adr/adr2013/13contentse.html\">European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road</a> and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.otif.org/en/publications/rid-2011.html\">Regulations concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Rail</a>. These authorisations carry conditions and time limits, and apply to carriage within Great Britain only. The authorisations can be withdrawn by the competent authority at any time by means of a written notice.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1362225\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/491780/453-continued-use-road-tank-vehicles.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/491780/thumbnail_453-continued-use-road-tank-vehicles.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a aria-describedby=\"attachment-1362225-accessibility-help\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/491780/453-continued-use-road-tank-vehicles.pdf\">Authorisation 453 (revision 1) and table of road tank vehicles: permitting the continued use of road tank vehicles manufactured by GRW Engineering</a></h2>\n    <p class=\"metadata\">\n        <span class=\"type\"><abbr title=\"Portable Document Format\">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class=\"file-size\">53.8KB</span>, <span class=\"page-length\">2 pages</span>\n    </p>\n\n\n      <div data-module=\"toggle\" class=\"accessibility-warning\" id=\"attachment-1362225-accessibility-help\">\n        <h2>This file may not be suitable for users of assistive technology.\n          <a class=\"toggler\" href=\"#attachment-1362225-accessibility-request\" data-controls=\"attachment-1362225-accessibility-request\" data-expanded=\"false\">Request an accessible format.</a>\n        </h2>\n        <p id=\"attachment-1362225-accessibility-request\" class=\"js-hidden\">\n          If you use assistive technology (such as a screen reader) and need a\nversion of this document in a more accessible format, please email <a href=\"mailto:webmasterdft@dft.gsi.gov.uk?body=Details%20of%20document%20required%3A%0A%0A%20%20Title%3A%20Authorisation%20453%20%28revision%201%29%20and%20table%20of%20road%20tank%20vehicles%3A%20permitting%20the%20continued%20use%20of%20road%20tank%20vehicles%20manufactured%20by%20GRW%20Engineering%0A%20%20Original%20format%3A%20pdf%0A%0APlease%20tell%20us%3A%0A%0A%20%201.%20What%20makes%20this%20format%20unsuitable%20for%20you%3F%0A%20%202.%20What%20format%20you%20would%20prefer%3F%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20&amp;subject=Request%20for%20%27Authorisation%20453%20%28revision%201%29%20and%20table%20of%20road%20tank%20vehicles%3A%20permitting%20the%20continued%20use%20of%20road%20tank